text: Acleris rosella is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in China. The wingspan is about 13 mm. The larvae feed on Rosa acicularis.Check List of the Tribe Tortricini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) in Northeast china, with Two Newly Recorded Species from China ==References== Category:Moths described in 1987 rosella Category:Moths of China
